## Important Rules

- **Score with evidence.** Every dimension score needs a one-line citation. No naked numbers.
- **Red lines are absolute.** A vendor that fails a red line does NOT pass even at a 4.9 aggregate.
- **Three-year horizon.** A vendor isn't a product, it's a relationship. Score that way.
- **Re-run quarterly for incumbents.** Vendor posture drifts. The whole point of this skill is to detect drift.
- **No vendor is the right vendor forever.** Always document the back-out path in the eval, even when recommending Proceed.
- **Read-only on vendor systems.** Never auth into a vendor's product without explicit ownership/auth.
